<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Afghan-Accord-Glance     04-14 0136</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Afghan-Accord-Glance,0144</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Provisions of Afghan Agreement</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Afghan-Signing, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here, at a glance, are the main features of the agreement to
withdraw Soviet troops from Afghanistan. The provisions, outlined
before the signing today in Geneva, include:
   
   _Withdrawal of all Soviet troops within nine months starting May
15, with half the total gone by Aug. 15.
   _Pledges by Pakistan and Afghanistan of non-interference in each
other's affairs.
   _Voluntary return of about 5 million Afghan refugees from
Pakistan and Iran.
   _Supervision of the settlement and the return of refugees by the
United Nations.
   _Guarantees from the United States and Soviet Union of
Afghanistan's future non-alignment.
   
   In addition, a U.S.-Soviet understanding will allow Washington
to continue military aid to the Afghan guerrillas, and Moscow to
continue sending arms to the Afghan government.
</TEXT>
