<HEAD>Gas-Like Smell Causes Evacuation Of Busy Shopping Street</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thousands of people were evacuated from one of
London's busiest shopping districts after an odor thought to be
caused by a gas leak permeated the area, police said.
   Three hours after clearing a 1 square mile area of Oxford Street
on Wednesday, city gas officials determined a gas leak had not
occurred. The cause of the smell was not determined, a police
spokesman said.
   The spokesman, who was not named in keeping with British custom,
said ``some theories were that it was sewage, another theory said
it was diesel (fuel oil) leaking from a bus, but no one knows.''
