<1ST_LINE>r a PM-Obit-Donnell     04-14 0190</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Obit-Donnell,0197</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Actress Jeff Donnell Dies of Heart Attack at 66</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Character actress Jeff Donnell, who portrayed
George Gobel's wife on the 1950s TV series, ``The George Gobel
Show'' and more recently appeared on the soap opera ``General
Hospital'' has died at age 66.
   Miss Donnell died Monday, after suffering an apparent a heart
attack at her Hollywood home, her son, Phineas Anderson, said
Wednesday.
   Miss Donnell, who acted in more than 50 films, was known most
recently to ``General Hospital'' fans as Stella Fields, the
Quartermaine family's housekeeper and Mrs. Quartermaine's partner
in a relish business, said Wendy Winter, an assistant to the
producer.
   Her movie roles included the ``Gidget'' films, ``The Blue
Gardenia,'' ``My Sister Eileen'' and ``Tora, Tora, Tora.''
   But she was best known for her role as Alice on ``The George
Gobel Show'' from 1954 to 1958.
   Miss Donnell's three marriages, to William R. Anderson, actor
Aldo Ray, and John Bricker, ended in divorce. She had been living
alone, Anderson said.
   In addition to her son, a Tucson, Ariz., resident, she is
survived by a daughter, Sally Durham, of Brisbane, Calif.
</TEXT>
