<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0429</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>April Storm Batters Central Atlantic Coast</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Strong wind and rain today battered the Atlantic Coast from
North Carolina to Maryland, while another storm drenched the desert
Southwest.
   Forecasters warned of continued high winds and coastal flooding
along the mid-Atlantic region, where strong winds and waves pushed
two homes into the sea and covered highways on Wednesday. Wind
gusted to 70 mph off Cape Hatteras, N.C.
   Salisbury, Md., had .47 inches of rain during a six-hour period
ending early today. Rain also fell over parts of Michigan,
Illinois, Iowa and southeast Nebraska.
   In the West, rain fell on Arizona, southeast California,
southern Utah, Nevada and the northern Pacific Coast. Las Vegas,
Nev., had .44 inches of rain during a six-hour period ended this
morning.
   Skies were clear or partly cloudy over much of the rest of the
nation.
   Kalispell, Mont., reached 74 degrees on Wednesday, tying its
high temperature record for the date set in 1913.
   Today's forecast called for rain scattered from the Pacific
Coast across the Great Basin and the Central Plateau; rain from the
lower Great Lakes across the upper Ohio Valley into western New
England; snow over upper Michigan; sunny skies over the remainder
of the nation.
   Highs were expected in the 60s or 70s across much of the nation;
40s and 50s from the northern Plains through the upper Mississippi
Valley and upper Great Lakes, much of the Ohio Valley and New
England; 30s from northeast Minnesota across upper Michigan; 80s
across the Arizona desert, Texas and the lower Mississippi Valley.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 21
degrees at Warroad, Minn., to 70 degrees at Laredo, Texas, and
Phoenix, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 54 fair; Boston 35 partly cloudy; Buffalo 49
cloudy; Charleston, S.C. 45 fair; Cincinnati 48 fair; Cleveland 55
cloudy; Detroit 56 rain; Miami 59 fair; New York 39 cloudy;
Philadelphia 38 partly cloudy; Pittsburgh 43 fair; Portland, Maine,
29 fair; Washington 38 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 24 fair; Chicago 48 partly cloudy;
Dallas-Fort Worth 55 fair; Denver 44 partly cloudy; Des Moines 40
fair; Indianapolis 53 cloudy; Kansas City 51 cloudy;
Minneapolis-St. Paul 35 fair; New Orleans 53 fair; St. Louis 57
partly cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque 60 cloudy; Anchorage 38 cloudy; Las Vegas 56
cloudy; Los Angeles 58 cloudy; Phoenix 69 cloudy; Salt Lake City 62
cloudy; San Diego 61 rain; San Francisco 53 showers; Seattle 50
cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 43 cloudy; Toronto 45 showers.
</TEXT>
