<HEAD>Explosion Rocks Downtown Johannesburg, No Reports Of Injuries</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An explosion rocked downtown
Johannesburg today, but there were no immediate reports of injuries
or damage.
   Police cordoned off a block in front of City Hall, where the
early evening blast apparently occurred.
   The cause of the explosion was not immediately clear, and police
at the scene refused to comment on the incident. The explosion at
about 6:30 p.m. (12:30 p.m. EDT) was heard and felt at the offices
of The Associated Press, about four blocks from City Hall.
   There was no sign of injuries or damage to the exterior of City
Hall.
   Lynn Wootton, 12, said he saw wisps of smoke rising from the
City Hall building shortly after the explosion. However, other
witnesses near City Hall at the time of the explosion said they
only felt the blast and did not see any smoke or evidence of damage.
