<HEAD>Tremors Destroy Hundreds of Homes in Iran</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Earthquakes in southern Iran have injured
30 people and destroyed 605 homes, 17 government offices and six
mosques in two weeks, Iran's official news agency said Thursday.
   The Islamic Republic News Agency, monitored in Cyprus, said the
quakes around the town of Behbehan about 360 miles south of Tehran
also killed cattle and damaged crops.
   It quoted the provincial governor, who was not identified, as
saying the tremors had been rocking the region since March 30 and
``quake-stricken villagers have been settled in 1,600 tents.''
   The agency did not give the magnitude of the tremors and
provided no further details.
