<HEAD>Musician George Rock Dead at 68</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHAMPAIGN, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   George Rock, a trumpet player and
vocalist best known for his recording of ``All I Want For Christmas
Is My Two Front Teeth,'' had died at the age of 68.
   Rock, who played the trumpet and clowned for nearly 15 years
with the group Spike Jones and the City Slickers, died Tuesday in
Burnham Hospital in Champaign, said hospital spokeswoman Shelly
Rueter.
   Ms. Rueter said a cause of death had not been released by the
hospital.
   After leaving the Jones band in 1960, Rock formed his own group,
playing Las Vegas and supplying music for network radio shows.
   Rock, who lived in Farmer City, is survived by a son and
daughter.
