<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
246,224 cars and trucks this week, up from last week's 202,120,
Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   Automakers produced 193,417 cars and trucks during the same week
a year ago. They were were scheduled to make 159,770 cars this
week, compared with 128,129 a week ago and 127,561 in the same week
in 1987.
